description:
Minimum Bill:
*Shall be the customer charge or such amount as may be required for line extension customers to justify the additional investment. 

Energy charge:
*Except those in excess of the greater of 60,000 kWh or 300 kWh per kW of measured demand @$0.0705 per kWh. 
*When the kW of measured load is above 6 kW, the $0.1093 per kWh is increased at the rate of:(1)120 kWh per kW of the first 19 kW over kW; (2)80 kWh per kW for the next 75 kW; (3)72 kWh per kW for All Additional kWh.


*Measured load: the average kW supplied during the 15 minute period of greatest use during the current month, but not less than the higher of: (1) the minimum kW specified in the Agreement, or (2) one-third of the capacity requirement.
*Capacity requirements: the highest kW of Measured Load established during the preceding eleven months, or the maximum kW specified in the Agreement, whichever is the greatest. In the even the instantaneous load of Customer's installation exceeds the Measured Load by more than fifty percent, such instantaneous load may be taken as the Capacity Requirements.
